  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting an integral management of water resources in Peru</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, Newcastle University will provide the scientific capacity and analysis in support of the overall water programme which aims to promote an integral and transparent management of water resources in Espinar and Ancash, two communities in the Peruvian highlands experiencing water stresses. 

The water programme aims to strengthen the capacity of community leaders, grass roots organisations and local authorities on technical issues related to participatory monitoring of water resources (quality and quantity) and legal and political issues related to the right to water. The programme also involves carrying out evidence-based research and participatory water mapping that will integrate scientific and indigenous knowledge. Ultimately, the programme aims to enable communities to enter into dialogue with government officials and private sector actors using the information they have received from the project as a tool to lobby for more transparent and appropriate use of water resources.</narrative>
  </description>
